ys atop the map, but also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the content that forms the base map."}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNShape","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNShape"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshape"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolylineFeature":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolylineFeature"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolylinefeature","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature","type":"topic","title":"MLNPolylineFeature","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object associates a polyline shape with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNMultiPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","type":"topic","title":"MLNMultiPolyline","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"type":"refe